Consolidated Edison, Inc. (ED) - Morgan Stanley Maintains Rating And Raises Price Target - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Consolidated Edison, Inc. (ED) – Morgan Stanley Maintains Rating And Raises Price Target
July 15, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Consolidated Edison, Inc. (NYSE:ED). 
  On June 13 the company was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” in a report from Jefferies. On October 24, 2016 the stock rating was changed to a “Hold” by Deutsche Bank which is up from the previous “Sell” rating.
 October 4 investment analysts at Citigroup made no change to the stock rating of “Neutral” but moved down the price target from $76.00 to $72.00. Equity analyst Evercore ISI Group started covering ED by announcing an initial rating of “Hold”.
 On September 21 Barclays left the company rating at “Equal-weight” and raised the price expectation  to $77.00 from $69.00.
 In the market the company is trading up by 0.50% since yesterday’s close of $80.33.  Additionally Consolidated Edison, Inc. recently announced a dividend which was paid on Thursday June 15th, 2017.  The dividend was $0.690 per share for the quarter which is $2.76 annualized.  This dividend represents a yeild of $3.40 which is the dividend as a percentage of the current share price.  The ex-dividend date was Monday the 15th of May 2017. 





 Shares last traded at $80.73 which is just a bit below the 50 day moving average of $82.41 and which is marginally over the 200 day moving average of $77.50.  The 50 day moving average was down by -2.03% whereas the 200 day average was up by +4.17%. 
 Consolidated Edison, Inc. (Con Edison), launched on September 3, 1997, is a holding company. The Company operates through its subsidiaries, which include Consolidated Edison Company of New York, Inc. (CECONY), Orange and Rockland Utilities, Inc. (O&R), Con Edison Clean Energy Businesses, Inc. (the Clean Energy Businesses) and Con Edison Transmission, Inc. (Con Edison Transmission). CECONY’s principal business operations are its regulated electric, gas and steam delivery businesses. O&R’s principal business operations are its regulated electric and gas delivery businesses. The Clean Energy Businesses develop, own and operate renewable and energy infrastructure projects and provide energy-related products and services to wholesale and retail customers. Con Edison Transmission, through its subsidiaries, invests in electric and gas transmission projects.. 
 The most current P/E ratio is 18.59 and the market cap of the company is 24.65B.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $4.34 and is projected to be $4.09 for the current year with 305,379,000 shares presently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $1.51 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $4.26. 






